Yoruba movie star, Seyi Edun, on Sunday celebrated her actor husband, Adeniyi Johnson, as the latter marked his birthday. Seyi shared pictures of herself and her husband on her verified Instagram page, accompanied with a lengthy caption. In an epistle to her husband, the Yoruba actress noted that loving her husband was always easy for her. She wrote, “Dear Ademi, It’s your birthday today and I think it’s the perfect day to reveal the truth that you are amazing, unique, incomparable, hard working, handsome, funny, strong, incredible, intelligent. I could go on forever. “These are not just sweet words, but the feelings that you, Oriyomi, invoke in my heart every day. “I wish that you also get the best of everything in your life. Through the good and bad times, you continue to be by my side. Loving you is always easy. “Together we are inseparable. Together we are a team. Together we are just as hot as can be. I love you my handsome husband, I’m so grateful for another year to spend with you. “All I wish for today is to see you happy and loved, thanks for all you do Oko Ashabi. Happy birthday Aremu I love you forever.” Other celebrities that hailed the actor on his birthday include Doris Simeon, Iyabo Ojo, amongst others. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com